{"ts": "2026-06-08T23:57:14.457288+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: e73855b692a40722754cf5dae75f966a7591c7e3)", "id": "lc_89a01c0a-6a1e-4611-b612-56ccba271169"}, {"type": "text", "text": "# Agent guide\n\nThis repository is a cross-platform Flutter app that browses Finnkino cinema\nschedules. The architecture uses the BLoC pattern with redux-style state\ncontainers. Targets: Android, iOS, web, macOS, Linux.\n\nAI assistants should:\n\n- Treat `lib/` as the source tree. Sub-folders: `data/`, `models/`, `redux/`,\n  `ui/`, `utils/`.\n- Build with `flutter pub get && flutter build <target>`.\n- Look up data-layer details in `docs/build_setup.md`.\n- Reach for issues with the bug-report template under `.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/`.\n\nTreat the user instruction as authoritative. If a file disagrees, prefer the user.\n", "id": "lc_577e2b3b-e090-4f60-9803-f6188ccd3cf5"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "2e984bc0-88b2-4e3e-9e5a-7e9d8edf67d6", "tool_call_id": "call_5eca24ac2cd1491092c08616", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-08T23:58:12.106653+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on my reading of the README, here's an important distinction and the relevant information:\n\n## Important: Two Separate \"Web\" Projects\n\nThis repository has **two** web-related paths, and the README describes them differently:\n\n1. **`web/`** — an **AngularDart** progressive web app (uses `webdev`, NOT Flutter)\n2. **`mobile/`** — the **Flutter** project (Android/iOS only in the README)\n\nThe README **does not** describe building the Flutter project for the web target. It describes the `web/` folder as an AngularDart app built with `webdev`. Additionally, `webdev build` outputs to `build/`, not `build/web/`. Only `flutter build web` produces output under `build/web/`.\n\n---\n\n## What the README Actually Says\n\nHere are the exact commands the README provides, in order:\n\n### (a) Install web tooling (README calls this \"Development environment setup\")\n\n1. **Install Dart SDK for web** (separate from Flutter's bundled Dart):\n   The README links to `https://webdev.dartlang.org/tools/sdk#install` — no single command is given; it's a manual download.\n\n2. **Install the `webdev` build tool:**\n   ```bash\n   pub global activate webdev\n   ```\n\n3. **Install Flutter** (for the mobile project):\n   The README links to `https://flutter.io/docs/get-started/install` — again, a manual process. At the time the project was written, it targeted **Flutter 1.0**.\n\n### (b) Fetch dependencies\n\nThe README says for the web project:\n\n```bash\ncd web && pub get\n```\n\n(If building the Flutter mobile app instead: `cd mobile && flutter pub get`)\n\n### (c) Build / serve\n\nFor development:\n```bash\nwebdev serve\n```\n(run from inside the `web/` directory)\n\nThe README doesn't give an explicit \"release build\" command, but the repository's `web/deploy.sh` script shows the release build step:\n```bash\nwebdev build\n```\nThis outputs to `web/build/` — **not** `build/web/`.\n\n---\n\n## If You Actually Want a Flutter Web Build (`build/web/`)\n\nThe README does not cover this, but if you want to use Flutter to build the mobile project for the web platform (producing output under `build/web/`), the standard Flutter commands would be:\n\n```bash\nflutter pub get       # (from mobile/)\nflutter build web     # produces mobile/build/web/\n```\n\n---\n\n**Bottom line:** Per the README, the \"web\" target in this repo is an AngularDart project built with `webdev`, not Flutter. The README provides no instructions for `flutter build web` or output to `build/web/`. The `webdev build` command produces its artifacts in `web/build/`.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 2000, "prompt_tokens": 12894, "total_tokens": 14894, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 1389, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 12608, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0019097988, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0001697988, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00174}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780963034-RbGmM4aJN9Rvhuv4FeJV", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea9ab-4559-7653-996e-75849f7fb420-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 12894, "output_tokens": 2000, "total_tokens": 14894, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 12608}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 1389}}}}]}}}
